Package: aims-os-security
Architecture: all
Multi-Arch: foreign
Depends:
 ${misc:Depends},
 aims-os-math,
# --- Cryptography (Post-Quantum Cryptography course) -----------------
# cryptography — modern primitives (AEAD, X.509, key derivation).
# pycryptodome — drop-in PyCrypto replacement; lecturers still
#     reference the PyCrypto API.
# NOTE: Qiskit (Quantum Mechanics and Computing) is intentionally NOT
# packaged — Debian's python3-qiskit is years behind upstream. Use
# `pipx install qiskit` or `mamba install -c conda-forge qiskit`.
 python3-cryptography,
 python3-pycryptodome,
# --- Ethical Hacking & Network Security ------------------------------
# Covers Ethical Hacking, Computer Security 1 (Network Security),
# Mathematical Model for Network Security, Auditing Computer Forensics.
# nmap — port / service scanner.
# wireshark + tcpdump — packet capture and analysis. dumpcap is
#     pre-configured setuid via build/config/preseed/wireshark.cfg.chroot
#     so non-root members of the wireshark group can capture.
# john + hashcat — password cracking (course requirement).
# aircrack-ng — Wi-Fi security auditing.
# sleuthkit + foremost + binwalk — disk / file-carving forensics.
# scapy — Python packet crafting; pairs with the Computer Network
#     course's protocol-design exercises.
 nmap,
 wireshark,
 tcpdump,
 john,
 hashcat,
 aircrack-ng,
 sleuthkit,
 foremost,
 binwalk,
 python3-scapy,
Description: AIMS OS — Coop Computer Security track
 Adds the cryptography, network-security and forensics tooling
 required by the AIMS Coop Computer Security filière on top of
 aims-os-math:
 .
 Cryptography primitives (python3-cryptography, python3-pycryptodome)
 for the Post-Quantum Cryptography course.
 .
 Network-security toolkit (nmap, Wireshark, tcpdump, John the Ripper,
 hashcat, aircrack-ng, scapy) for the Ethical Hacking, Computer
 Security I: Network Security, and Mathematical Model for Network
 Security courses.
 .
 Disk-forensics toolkit (Sleuth Kit, foremost, binwalk) for the
 Auditing Computer Forensics and Investigation course.
 .
 Qiskit (Quantum Mechanics and Computing course) is install-on-demand
 via `pipx install qiskit` or `mamba install -c conda-forge qiskit` —
 the Debian package lags upstream by years and the course needs the
 current API.
 .
 This metapackage Depends on aims-os-math, so installing it on a
 vanilla Debian Trixie pulls the full SciPy / R / LaTeX scientific
 stack as well. Regular-track students who don't need security tooling
 should install aims-os-math directly.
 .
 Wireshark's dumpcap is setuid (so non-root members of the wireshark
 group can capture packets) when installed via the AIMS OS ISO. When
 installed via the AIMS OS apt repo onto a vanilla Debian, you'll be
 prompted by debconf during install — answer "yes" for the same
 behaviour, then add yourself to the wireshark group:
   sudo usermod -aG wireshark $USER && newgrp wireshark
